Speaking about dating a non-tennis pro last year, Berdych said: ‘Actually, yes, I see a big difference.

'I mean, in the past I was saying that it's probably the best thing just that we are both from the same thing. I didn't have any other experience.

‘But now I can say that this one is way better because, you know, I think it was too much tennis. 

'If you do it like myself, and I'm dealing with everyday work that you have to play, practise, organise this stuff, then winning, losing, handle this situation, it's quite tough to have it from one side. 

'If you have to deal with the same thing from the other side, it was quite too much.

He added: 'So I'm really enjoying that, that it's different, that I met somebody with a different life. It's a nice experience.’

